video.title: Community
video.synopsis: When his bogus law degree is exposed, Jeff Winger goes back to college and forms a study group of outcasts. (One episode of Season 2 is not available.)

episodes.synopsis: When the legitimacy of his degree is challenged, lawyer Jeff Winger must return to school, where he meets a clan of misfit community college students.
episodes.title: Community

episodes.synopsis: While Jeff looks to use a Spanish class assignment to get close to Britta, Pierce has something altogether different in mind.
episodes.title: Spanish 101

episodes.synopsis: Jeff struggles to get a good grade, and Britta's offer to bankroll his film class exposes a rift between Abed and his angry father.
episodes.title: Introduction to Film

episodes.synopsis: As Annie recruits Abed and Troy for a psychology class experiment, Jeff and Shirley bond over their mutual fondness for gossip.
episodes.title: Social Psychology

episodes.synopsis: As Pierce volunteers to compose a new school song, a cheating episode in Spanish class leaves Jeff defending Britta before a disciplinary tribunal.
episodes.title: Advanced Criminal Law

episodes.synopsis: Annie's dream of being the ex-football star's girlfriend is in jeopardy when Jeff is blackmailed into getting Troy to join Greendale's football team.
episodes.title: Football, Feminism and You

episodes.synopsis: Jeff sets his sights on an attractive professor, and Annie looks to boost her social standing by hosting a Day of the Dead party.
episodes.title: Introduction to Statistics

episodes.synopsis: Jeff is forced out of his condo and into Abed's dorm room, and Annie looks to get Troy's attention by helping him plan a romantic picnic.
episodes.title: Home Economics

episodes.synopsis: As Jeff is drafted to help lead Greendale's debate team against the formidable City College, Abed's film-class projects appear to predict the future.
episodes.title: Debate 109

episodes.synopsis: Faced with an unreasonable amount of Spanish homework, Jeff's efforts to handle Señor Chang manage to help him, but not the rest of the class.
episodes.title: Environmental Science

episodes.synopsis: With his high-price "escort" girlfriend on his arm, Pierce pressures Jeff into asking Dean Pelton's airhead secretary to double date at the STD Fair.
episodes.title: The Politics of Human Sexuality

episodes.synopsis: Shirley's plans for a holiday party are in jeopardy when Jeff is drawn into a fight with a campus bully.
episodes.title: Comparative Religion

episodes.synopsis: Jeff accepts an invitation to be the editor of the school paper as he and his friends fend off an interloper who wants to join their study group.
episodes.title: Investigative Journalism

episodes.synopsis: As Jeff and Prof. Slater try to keep their student-teacher romance under wraps, Britta and Troy tell everyone about their shared passion for dance.
episodes.title: Interpretive Dance

episodes.synopsis: Jeff and Britta team up to derail Annie's fledgling romance with Greendale's resident hippie singer-songwriter, Vaughn.
episodes.title: Romantic Expressionism

episodes.synopsis: As Valentine's Day finds Jeff struggling with his feelings for Britta and professor Slater, Pierce and Troy are wrongly blamed for a prank.
episodes.title: Communication Studies

episodes.synopsis: The study group helps Abed land a date with a girl, and Jeff squares off with a P.E. coach who insists that he wear gym shorts to a billiards class.
episodes.title: Physical Education

episodes.synopsis: As Family Day lands Jeff in the middle of an affair with Pierce's sexy ex-stepdaughter, Shirley's unruly sons help liberate Abed's Afghani cousin.
episodes.title: Basic Genealogy

episodes.synopsis: A pottery class he takes for an easy A reveals Jeff's deep-seated need to succeed.
episodes.title: Beginner Pottery

episodes.synopsis: When her April Fools' Day prank inadvertently sends a human cadaver out the anatomy lab window, Britta looks to place the blame on Jeff.
episodes.title: The Science of Illusion

episodes.synopsis: A scheme to replace a corrupt cafeteria employee transforms the study group into a criminal gang run by a power-hungry Abed.
episodes.title: Contemporary American Poultry

episodes.synopsis: While a tasteless prank ends with Pierce being tossed out of the group, Britta and Jeff are forced to team up against some teen newcomers at school.
episodes.title: The Art of Discourse

episodes.synopsis: The first prize of priority registration engulfs Greendale Community College in a Spring Fling paintball war.
episodes.title: Modern Warfare

episodes.synopsis: On the eve of an important final exam in Spanish, everyone's grades are jeopardized when it is discovered that Señor Chang has a damaging secret.
episodes.title: English as a Second Language

episodes.synopsis: As the end of the school year finds Jeff at the apex of a romantic triangle, Annie ponders moving away with her hacky sack-playing boyfriend.
episodes.title: Pascal's Triangle Revisited

episodes.synopsis: When the semester starts, Jeff is stunned that his rejection of Britta has made her a campus star; Chang wants to be accepted into the study group.
episodes.title: Anthropology 101

episodes.synopsis: When an old friend from Jeff's past appears unexpectedly, his friends discover that he was the one responsible for Jeff's disbarment.
episodes.title: Accounting for Lawyers

episodes.synopsis: A death provokes a fierce debate about Pierce's religious beliefs. Britta and Annie are at odds over tactics in the Gulf oil spill fund-raising drive.
episodes.title: The Psychology of Letting Go

episodes.synopsis: Jeff and the group must salvage an aging museum exhibit that Dean Pelton wants as the centerpiece of Greendale's proposed aerospace training program.
episodes.title: Basic Rocket Science

episodes.synopsis: Shirley and Abed are at odds over his plan to direct and star in his own epic religious film.
episodes.title: Messianic Myths and Ancient Peoples

episodes.synopsis: Dean Pelton's army surplus party food sparks an outbreak of zombie-ism at the Greendale Halloween party.
episodes.title: Epidemiology

episodes.synopsis: Abed endears himself to the girls after he offers to take down their enemies on campus; Jeff and Troy stumble onto a groundskeeper's secret paradise.
episodes.title: Aerodynamics of Gender

episodes.synopsis: Annie's missing pen leads to friction within the group.
episodes.title: Cooperative Calligraphy

episodes.synopsis: When Jeff tries to obtain credit for a fictitious class, the unintended consequences rock Greendale. Abed and Troy build an elaborate blanket fort.
episodes.title: Conspiracy Theories and Interior Design

episodes.synopsis: Troy's friends help him celebrate his 21st birthday.
episodes.title: Mixology Certification

episodes.synopsis: The meaning of Christmas is lost and Abed's intense fixation on the holiday concerns the group in this special stop-motion animation episode.
episodes.title: Abed's Uncontrollable Christmas

episodes.synopsis: With Chang pressing for membership in the study group, Annie's latest crush has Jeff reeling as Shirley unveils some stunning news.
episodes.title: Asian Population Studies

episodes.synopsis: Pierce's efforts to bribe director Annie may undermine the theater group's antidrug play; Jeff's texting prank puts Britta in an awkward situation.
episodes.title: Celebrity Pharmacology

episodes.synopsis: On Valentine's Day, Troy and Abed compete for the attention of an assistant librarian, while Britta tries to show she's open-minded about lesbians.
episodes.title: Early 21st Century Romanticism

episodes.synopsis: Claiming that he is about to die, Pierce summons the study group to the hospital to bequeath his belongings to them.
episodes.title: Intermediate Documentary Filmmaking

episodes.synopsis: For an upcoming vice-presidential visit, Glendale's Dean Pelton hastily organizes an election for student body president that pits Annie against Jeff.
episodes.title: Intro to Political Science

episodes.synopsis: Although Shirley and Andre don't want Chang involved with her baby, he resolves to be a good dad. Abed and Troy's new friend may be a war criminal.
episodes.title: Custody Law and Eastern European Diplomacy

episodes.synopsis: Jeff and the group arrange a Pulp Fiction birthday party for Abed, but he has his own plans, starting with an expensive dinner for himself and Jeff.
episodes.title: Critical Film Studies

episodes.synopsis: Jeff is suspicious of Pierce's engagement to a pretty classmate. Troy invents a childhood trauma to impress Britta, and Abed challenges a professor.
episodes.title: Competitive Wine Tasting

episodes.synopsis: Working on their final anthropology diorama, Chang finds a cache of items stolen by Troy's monkey that dredge up unhappy memories for the study group.
episodes.title: Paradigms of Human Memory

episodes.synopsis: As the semester ends, the anthropology final is disrupted when Shirley goes into labor and her husband, Andre, is summoned to school for the birth.
episodes.title: Applied Anthropology and Culinary Arts

episodes.synopsis: A $100,000 paintball war prize pits members of the study group against one another, until they decide to join forces to stop a mysterious challenger.
episodes.title: A Fist Full of Paintballs

episodes.synopsis: As the paintball war is revealed to be a City College plot, Jeff and Troy vie for control of Greendale's ragtag army, while Pierce betrays the group.
episodes.title: For a Few Paintballs More

episodes.synopsis: As Jeff tries to keep Pierce from rejoining the study group, Dean Pelton faces off with Vice Dean Laybourne for control of Greendale.
episodes.title: Biology 101

episodes.synopsis: As Annie competes with an overachieving rival in a Model United Nations competition, Jeff wrestles with his feelings for his ambitious friend.
episodes.title: Geography of Global Conflict

episodes.synopsis: The study group struggles to incorporate a fellow classmate while working on a project for Professor Kane's class.
episodes.title: Competitive Ecology

episodes.synopsis: When Jeff introduces an element of randomness into Troy and Abed's housewarming party, reality splits into six timelines.
episodes.title: Remedial Chaos Theory

episodes.synopsis: When a personality test suggests that one group member is a homicidal maniac, they use a series of scary Halloween stories to expose the killer.
episodes.title: Horror Fiction in Seven Spooky Steps

episodes.synopsis: When a drag queen's song makes Hawthorne Wipes an iconic gay product, Pierce embraces it, until his homophobic dad shows up to squelch the idea.
episodes.title: Advanced Gay

episodes.synopsis: Annie has second thoughts about moving in with Troy and Abed once she realizes that they expect her to live in a blanket fort.
episodes.title: Studies in Modern Movement

episodes.synopsis: As Dean Pelton films a new commercial for Greendale, the production takes a wild turn once he discovers that a famous alum has agreed to appear in it.
episodes.title: Documentary Filmmaking: Redux

episodes.synopsis: When Shirley agrees to coach Jeff in foosball, they realize that she bullied him mercilessly when they were kids.
episodes.title: Foosball and Nocturnal Vigilantism

episodes.synopsis: The study group is slowly convinced to fill in for the Glee Club at Greendale's Christmas pageant.
episodes.title: Regional Holiday Music

episodes.synopsis: When Shirley's remarriage to Andre threatens to put her dreams of starting a business with Pierce on hold, Britta steps in.
episodes.title: Urban Matrimony and the Sandwich Arts

episodes.synopsis: The study group must work as celebrity impersonators at a bar mitzvah to pay off Abed's debt to a talent agency owner.
episodes.title: Contemporary Impressionists

episodes.synopsis: When Britta falls for the human embodiment of the Subway sandwich chain, Shirley and Pierce hope to use the situation to their advantage.
episodes.title: Digital Exploration of Interior Design

episodes.synopsis: The students of Greendale are drawn into an epic pillow fight as Troy and Abed start a war that threatens to destroy their unique friendship.
episodes.title: Pillows and Blankets

episodes.synopsis: When a carnival comes to Greendale, Annie goes to great lengths to make sure that Britta doesn't contact her carnival worker ex-boyfriend.
episodes.title: Origins of Vampire Mythology

episodes.synopsis: After sending Troy and Britta on a date, Annie volunteers to keep Abed company in his Dreamatorium.
episodes.title: Virtual Systems Analysis

episodes.synopsis: When the yam the study group was growing for biology class is killed, Troy and Abed are on the case.
episodes.title: Basic Lupine Urology

episodes.synopsis: After a classmate suddenly dies, the study group decides to host a memorial, but Jeff turns his speech into an angry anti-Greendale rant.
episodes.title: Course Listing Unavailable

episodes.synopsis: After Abed is caught trespassing at Greendale, he and his friends visit a psychiatrist.
episodes.title: Curriculum Unavailable

episodes.synopsis: Pierce and his closest friends are summoned to Hawthorne Labs to play a video game that will determine who will inherit his father's fortune.
episodes.title: Digital Estate Planning

episodes.synopsis: The study group stages an elaborate heist to break in to Greendale and free Dean Pelton (Jim Rash) from the clutches of Chang (Ken Jeong).
episodes.title: The First Chang Dynasty

episodes.synopsis: Jeff agrees to represent Shirley in a case against Pierce to determine official ownership of their new sandwich shop.
episodes.title: Introduction to Finality

episodes.synopsis: On the first day of senior year, Jeff reveals some news that might tear apart the study group. Meanwhile, Dean Pelton holds an elaborate competition.
episodes.title: History 101

episodes.synopsis: On the way to a Halloween party, the study group must free Pierce from his panic room and slowly comes to suspect that his mansion is haunted.
episodes.title: Paranormal Parentage

episodes.synopsis: Troy worries about losing Abed to a fellow Inspector Spacetime fan at a convention for the show, while Annie fantasizes about being married to Jeff.
episodes.title: Conventions of Space and Time

episodes.synopsis: The study group contends with a group of German students who take over the study room. Chang makes his return to campus.
episodes.title: Alternative History of the German Invasion

episodes.synopsis: Britta joins Jeff to see his estranged father on Thanksgiving. Shirley invites the rest of the group to spend the holiday with her judgmental in-laws.
episodes.title: Cooperative Escapism in Familial Relations

episodes.synopsis: Greendale comes together to get to the bottom of Chang's amnesia, which Abed films as a documentary. Jeff, however, suspects Chang is faking it.
episodes.title: Advanced Documentary Filmmaking

episodes.synopsis: Dean Pelton enlists the study group to beautify the campus to woo a wealthy student to Greendale. A class on teaching P.E. pits Shirley against Troy.
episodes.title: Economics of Marine Biology

episodes.synopsis: Jeff sets out to embarrass Britta when she announces a dance for women's empowerment. Abed dreams of shuttling between two dates in one night.
episodes.title: Herstory of Dance

episodes.synopsis: Dean Pelton prompts the study group to use puppets to relive the traumatic events of a recent adventure.
episodes.title: Intro to Felt Surrogacy

episodes.synopsis: Jeff organizes a lovely holiday gathering at his apartment, but Annie secretly invites Professor Cornwallis to get in his good graces.
episodes.title: Intro to Knots

episodes.synopsis: When Annie and Shirley learn that Leonard is actually holding the spot as the class valedictorian, they join forces to bring him down.
episodes.title: Basic Human Anatomy

episodes.synopsis: Abed's research into the study group's history uncovers an overlooked series of chance encounters that led each of them to Greendale.
episodes.title: Heroic Origins

episodes.synopsis: A plan to celebrate Jeff's early graduation is unexpectedly disrupted by the study group's evil doppelgangers from the Darkest Timeline.
episodes.title: Advanced Introduction to Finality

episodes.synopsis: With his law practice doomed, Jeff returns to Greendale to start a class action suit against the school, but a hologram of Pierce has him reconsider.
episodes.title: Repilot

episodes.synopsis: Abed tackles a two-day crash course on Nicolas Cage, while a clueless Jeff begins his teaching career with Annie as his most demanding student.
episodes.title: Introduction to Teaching

episodes.synopsis: With the mysterious Ass Crack Bandit back at Greendale, Annie and Jeff are on the case. As clues and suspicions mount, Shirley delivers shocking news.
episodes.title: Basic Intergluteal Numismatics

episodes.synopsis: Pierce's funeral leaves the study group with mixed feelings, especially after their late tormentor leaves one last test to reveal everyone's secrets.
episodes.title: Cooperative Polygraphy

episodes.synopsis: For Troy's last day at Greendale, Abed holds a campus-wide "hot lava" fantasy game. With a comic book worth $50,000 as the prize, it's an all-out war.
episodes.title: Geothermal Escapism

episodes.synopsis: While Annie and Hickey's fight to get a bulletin board repaired spirals out of control, Abed and Britta go to war over spoilers of his favorite show.
episodes.title: Analysis of Cork-Based Networking

episodes.synopsis: Jeff counsels a smitten Duncan on how to get a date with Britta but is developing feelings of his own. An angry Hickey tries to teach Abed a lesson.
episodes.title: Bondage and Beta Male Sexuality

episodes.synopsis: A new caste system takes over when Greendale beta tests an app that ranks everyone. Shirley loves her new status, but Jeff and Britta want it stopped.
episodes.title: App Development and Condiments

episodes.synopsis: Abed and Annie try to solve their new roommate dilemma with a retro VCR game, while Jeff, Shirley and Hickey hatch a plan to sell stolen textbooks.
episodes.title: VCR Maintenance and Educational Publishing

episodes.synopsis: To help Hickey be a more involved grandfather, which means patching up a bad relationship with his son, the gang creates an epic role-playing game.
episodes.title: Advanced Advanced Dungeons & Dragons

episodes.synopsis: Jeff's depression over turning 40 leads him to drink himself unconscious. In his dreams, he and the gang are part of the "G. I. Joe" cartoon team.
episodes.title: G.I. Jeff

episodes.synopsis: The Save Greendale Committee's success is short-lived when the board votes for a corporate sellout, but Pelton, Annie and Abed might find a solution.
episodes.title: Basic Story

episodes.synopsis: To save Greendale from being sold, the gang searches for an eccentric computer science professor's legendary treasure hidden beneath the school.
episodes.title: Basic Sandwich

episodes.synopsis: New administrative consultant Frankie's strict — and sobering — changes split the group when Abed goes rogue to side with the enemy.
episodes.title: Ladders

episodes.synopsis: When Dean Pelton loses himself — and a chunk of the college budget — in a virtual reality system, Jeff seeks help from its cantankerous inventor.
episodes.title: Lawnmower Maintenance & Postnatal Care

episodes.synopsis: A rival's attack ad puts the group into defensive mode — and a moral quandary. Britta and Chang find new ways to gross everyone out.
episodes.title: Basic Crisis Room Decorum

episodes.synopsis: Dean Pelton's sexuality gives him an uncomfortable edge for a school board seat. Chang scores a surprise win in a stage adaptation of "The Karate Kid."
episodes.title: Queer Studies & Advanced Waxing

episodes.synopsis: When prisoners roll into Greendale via telerobot, Jeff meets his match in a clever convict. Britta's plans for a raging house party backfire.
episodes.title: Laws Of Robotics & Party Rights

episodes.synopsis: A hacker angry over a racist comic's planned campus performance threatens to publish the activity committee's personal emails.
episodes.title: Basic Email Security

episodes.synopsis: Britta's ex-boyfriend, Rick, returns, reigniting her far-fetched dreams of a normal relationship. Annie goes to extremes to win Elroy over.
episodes.title: Advanced Safety Feature

episodes.synopsis: A commercial catchphrase catapults Chang to viral fame and a life-changing move. The group bands together to make movie magic for Abed.
episodes.title: Intro To Recycled Cinema

episodes.synopsis: Visiting Professor DeSalvo gives Jeff and his friends a master class in grifting and a bonus lesson on the art of revenge.
episodes.title: Grifting 101

episodes.synopsis: A 19-foot plaster hand guides the group on an emotional journey as they travel through mountains and flashbacks while aboard Elroy's RV.
episodes.title: Basic RV Repair & Palmistry

episodes.synopsis: Heroes are born, promises are broken and the stakes are raised when paintball makes an explosive return to Greendale's campus.
episodes.title: Modern Espionage

episodes.synopsis: When two Greendale students get married, the wedding reception takes a turn after Jeff unwittingly exposes an inconvenient truth.
episodes.title: Wedding Videography

episodes.synopsis: The former study group's future — and friendships — are put to a test when one chapter of their lives closes and a new one begins.
episodes.title: Emotional Consequences of Broadcast Television
